.TH "i915_vma_bind" 9 "i915_vma_bind" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
i915_vma_bind \- Sets up PTEs for an VMA in it's corresponding address space.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" i915_vma_bind
.BI "(struct i915_vma *vma "  ","
.BI "enum i915_cache_level cache_level "  ","
.BI "u32 flags "  ","
.BI "struct i915_vma_work *work "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "vma" 12
VMA to map
.IP "cache_level" 12
mapping cache level
.IP "flags" 12
flags like global or local mapping
.IP "work" 12
preallocated worker for allocating and binding the PTE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
DMA addresses are taken from the scatter-gather table of this object (or of
this VMA in case of non-default GGTT views) and PTE entries set up.
Note that DMA addresses are also the only part of the SG table we care about.
